OL,3,CCommons Speaker Sir Lindsay Hoyle
OL,4,Cunder pressure - what happens next?
OL,6,FWhen he took up the role he said it
OL,7,Fwould be "an honour" to serve in
OL,8,FParliament, and added that the Speaker
OL,9,Fmust be "trusted".
OL,11,F"I've a proven track record of being
OL,12,Fimpartial, independent and fair," he
OL,13,Fsaid at the time.
OL,15,FThe Speaker must be politically
OL,16,Fimpartial so must resign from the
OL,17,Fpolitical party and remain separate
OL,18,Ffrom political issues once appointed
OL,19,Fto the role.
OL,21,FWill Sir Lindsay Hoyle be sacked?
