OL,3,CCommons Speaker Sir Lindsay Hoyle
OL,4,Cunder pressure - what happens next?
OL,6,FSNP and Conservative party members
OL,7,Fcame together in criticism of Sir
OL,8,FLindsay on Wednesday, and they are
OL,9,Fexpected to continue to express their
OL,10,Funhappiness on Thursday.
OL,12,FTory MPs are poised to urge Commons
OL,13,FLeader Penny Mordaunt to sanction a no-
OL,14,Fconfidence vote in the Speaker on
OL,15,FThursday.
OL,17,FAs leader of the House Ms Mordaunt,
OL,18,Falong with Tory Chief Whip Simon Hart,
OL,19,Fhas to grant parliamentary time for a
OL,20,Fno-confidence vote to take place.
