OL,3,CCommons Speaker Sir Lindsay Hoyle
OL,4,Cunder pressure - what happens next?
OL,6,FAn overwhelming majority in a no-
OL,7,Fconfidence vote would typically prompt
OL,8,Fa government official to resign.
OL,10,FHow would a new Speaker be chosen?
OL,12,FA new Speaker is elected by secret
OL,13,Fballot and they must also be re-
OL,14,Felected after each general election.
OL,16,FIf a candidate receives more than 50%
OL,17,Fof the votes, their election to the
OL,18,Frole as Speaker is put to the House as
OL,19,Fa question.
